<section>
<title>Compactness</title>

<definition>
  <statement>
    <p>A set <m>K \subset \mathbb{R}</m> is <term>compact</term> if every sequences in <m>K</m> has a subsequence that converges in <m>K</m>.</p>
  </statement>
</definition>

<example>
  <title><m>[0,1]</m> is compact</title>
  <p>Consider <m>K=[0,1] \subset \mathbb{R}</m>.  We want to show that <m>K</m> is compact.</p>
